# GOLDEN-CROSS a.adl::RA b.adl::RB DISJOINT
# GROUND-TRUTH: a's jets (pt>100) refine b's jets (pt>30) over the shared
# base Jet, so size(a jets) <= size(b jets) (XSUB). RA needs >= 3 tight
# jets while RB allows <= 2 loose ones: 3 <= |A| <= |B| <= 2 is absurd in
# every event, so the pair is disjoint ACROSS the two analyses.
object jets
  take Jet
  select pt > 100
region RA
  select size(jets) >= 3
